SENATE BILL 489
J2 6lr3472
By: Senator Lam Senators Lam, Lewis Young, Beidle, Hayes, and A. Washington
Introduced and read first time: February 2, 2026
Assigned to: Finance
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 6, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Health Occupations – Physicians Trained in International Medical Schools
3 Foreign Countries – Exemption From Educational Requirements and Limited
4 License
5 FOR the purpose of establishing that certain applicants for a physician license are exempt
6 from certain educational requirements if the applicant submits certain evidence of
7 international postgraduate medical education training accredited by a certain entity;
8 authorizing certain licensed physicians trained in international medical schools to
9 practice medicine during their initial license term only under supervision; altering
10 the exemption from certain educational requirements required for a license to
11 practice medicine for certain applicants who have studied at an international
12 medical school; authorizing the State Board of Physicians to issue a limited license
13 to practice medicine to a physician trained and licensed in a foreign country under
14 certain circumstances; and generally relating to physicians trained in international
15 medical schools foreign countries.
16 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
17 Article – Health Occupations
18 Section 14–101(a)
19 Annotated Code of Maryland
20 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
21 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
22 Article – Health Occupations
23 Section 14–308(b)(6)(i) and 14–314(a) 14–101(g) and 14–308
