8 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
9 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
10 Article – Health Occupations
11 14–308.
12 (b) An applicant for a license is exempt from the educational requirements of §
13 14–307 of this subtitle, if the applicant:
14 (6) Meets one of the following requirements:
15 (i) The applicant graduated from any international medical school
16 and submits evidence acceptable to the Board of successful completion of 2 years of training
17 in a postgraduate medical education program accredited by [an] THE ACCREDITATION
18 COUNCIL FOR GRADUATE MEDICAL EDUCATION–INTERNATIONAL (ACGME–I) OR
19 ANOTHER accrediting organization recognized by the Board; or
20 14–314.
21 (a) (1) [Except] SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION AND
22 EXCEPT as otherwise provided in this title, a license authorizes the licensee to practice
23 medicine while the license is effective.
24 (2) A LICENSEE WHO QUALIFIES UNDER § 14–308(B)(6)(I) OF THIS
25 SUBTITLE MAY PRACTICE MEDICINE DURING THE LICENSEE’S INITIAL LICENSE
26 TERM ONLY UNDER SUPERVISION, AS REQUIRED BY THE BOARD.
27 14–101.
28 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
29 (g) (1) “License” means, unless the context requires otherwise, a license issued
30 by the Board to practice medicine or an allied health profession regulated by the Board.
31 (2) “LICENSE” INCLUDES, UNLESS THE CONTEXT REQUIRES
32 OTHERWISE, A LIMITED LICENSE ISSUED UNDER § 14–308 OF THIS TITLE.

SENATE BILL 489 3
1 [14–308.] 14–307.1.
2 [(a) (1) In this section the following terms have the meanings indicated.
3 (2) “Fifth pathway program” means a program that the Board approves in
4 its regulations for a student who:
