6 (ii) Was a United States citizen when the student enrolled in the
7 international medical school; and
8 (iii) Has completed all of the formal requirements for graduation
9 from the international medical school, except for any social service or postgraduate
10 requirements.
11 (3) “International medical school” means a medical school located outside
12 of the United States, its territories or possessions, Puerto Rico, or Canada.
13 (b)] An applicant for a license is exempt from the educational requirements of §
14 14–307 of this subtitle, if the applicant:
