11 14–308.
12 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “HEALTH CARE FACILITY” MEANS:
13 (1) A LOCAL HEALTH DEPARTMENT;
14 (2) A SCHOOL OF MEDICINE;
15 (3) A FEDERALLY QUALIFIED HEALTH CENTER;
16 (4) A HEALTH SYSTEM;
17 (5) A HOSPITAL;
18 (6) A HOSPITAL–BASED FACILITY; OR
19 (7) A FREESTANDING EMERGENCY FACILITY.
20 (B) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO A PHYSICIAN WHO:
21 (1) HAS COMPLETED:
22 (I) A RESIDENCY ACCREDITED BY THE ACCREDITATION
23 COUNCIL FOR GRADUATE MEDICAL EDUCATION;
24 (II) A RESIDENCY ACCREDITED BY THE AMERICAN
25 OSTEOPATHIC ASSOCIATION; OR
26 (III) ROYAL COLLEGE OF PHYSICIANS AND SURGEONS
27 ACCREDITED RESIDENCY TRAINING IN CANADA; OR

SENATE BILL 489 5
1 (2) PREVIOUSLY HELD A MEDICAL LICENSE ISSUED IN THE UNITED
2 STATES OR CANADA.
3 (C) BEGINNING OCTOBER 1, 2028, THE BOARD MAY ISSUE A LIMITED
4 LICENSE TO PRACTICE MEDICINE TO A PHYSICIAN TRAINED AND LICENSED IN A
5 FOREIGN COUNTRY WHO MEETS THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION.
6 (D) TO BE ELIGIBLE FOR A LIMITED LICENSE UNDER THIS SECTION, AN
7 APPLICANT SHALL:
8 (1) BE OF GOOD MORAL CHARACTER;
9 (2) HAVE RECEIVED A DEGREE OF DOCTOR OF MEDICINE OR ITS
10 EQUIVALENT FROM A MEDICAL SCHOOL LOCATED OUTSIDE THE UNITED STATES
11 WITH RECOGNIZED ACCREDITATION STATUS FROM THE EDUCATIONAL
12 COMMISSION FOR FOREIGN MEDICAL GRADUATES;
13 (3) HAVE COMPLETED AT LEAST 2 YEARS OF TRAINING IN A
14 RESIDENCY PROGRAM:
15 (I) ACCREDITED BY THE AMERICAN COUNCIL FOR GRADUATE
16 MEDICAL EDUCATION – INTERNATIONAL;
17 (II) IN A COUNTRY WHOSE GRADUATE MEDICAL EDUCATION
18 ACCREDITING AGENCY HAS BEEN RECOGNIZED BY THE WORLD FEDERATION FOR
19 MEDICAL EDUCATION; OR
20 (III) ACCREDITED BY ANOTHER ACCREDITATION AUTHORITY
21 APPROVED BY THE BOARD;
22 (4) (I) HAVE BEEN IN GOOD STANDING WITH THE MEDICAL
23 LICENSING OR REGULATORY AUTHORITY IN THE FOREIGN COUNTRY AT THE TIME
24 OF THE APPLICANT’S DEPARTURE; OR
25 (II) IF REASONABLE ATTEMPTS TO OBTAIN THE INDIVIDUAL’S
26 LICENSURE STATUS HAVE BEEN UNSUCCESSFUL, BE APPROVED BY THE BOARD ON
27 AN INDIVIDUAL BASIS;
28 (5) HAVE NO PENDING DISCIPLINARY MATTERS BEFORE A LICENSING
29 OR REGULATORY BODY;
30 (6) HAVE AN OFFER OF EMPLOYMENT WITH A PARTICIPATING
31 HEALTH CARE FACILITY THAT WILL EVALUATE THE APPLICANT’S NONCLINICAL

6 SENATE BILL 489
1 SKILLS AND FAMILIARITY WITH STANDARDS APPROPRIATE FOR MEDICAL PRACTICE
2 IN THE STATE; AND
3 (7) SATISFY ANY OTHER REQUIREMENTS ESTABLISHED BY THE
4 BOARD IN REGULATION, INCLUDING PRIOR PRACTICE EXPERIENCE.
5 (E) THE BOARD MAY DETERMINE AN APPLICANT INELIGIBLE FOR A
6 LIMITED LICENSE IF THE APPLICANT:
7 (1) WAS SUBJECT TO PREVIOUS DISCIPLINARY ACTION;
8 (2) HAD DISCIPLINE OR COMPETENCY PROBLEMS DURING THE
9 APPLICANT’S POSTGRADUATE TRAINING; OR
10 (3) FAILS TO SUBMIT EVIDENCE ACCEPTABLE TO THE BOARD THAT
11 THE APPLICANT MEETS THE REQUIREMENTS FOR A LIMITED LICENSE.
12 (F) TO APPLY FOR A LIMITED LICENSE, AN APPLICANT SHALL:
13 (1) SUBMIT AN APPLICATION TO THE BOARD ON THE FORM THAT THE
14 BOARD REQUIRES; AND
15 (2) PAY TO THE BOARD AN APPLICATION FEE SET BY THE BOARD.
16 (G) (1) THE TERM OF A LIMITED LICENSE MAY NOT EXCEED 3 YEARS.
17 (2) A LIMITED LICENSE MAY NOT BE RENEWED.
18 (H) A LIMITED LICENSE AUTHORIZES THE HOLDER TO PRACTICE MEDICINE
19 ONLY:
20 (1) WHILE EMPLOYED IN FULL–TIME EMPLOYMENT BY THE HEALTH
21 CARE FACILITY DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (D)(6) OF THIS SECTION; AND
22 (2) IN THE EMPLOYING HEALTH CARE FACILITY OR A HEALTH CARE
23 FACILITY OPERATED BY THE EMPLOYING HEALTH CARE FACILITY.
24 (I) THE BOARD MAY REVOKE A LIMITED LICENSE ISSUED UNDER THIS
25 SECTION IF:
26 (1) THE LICENSEE PRACTICES OUTSIDE THE SCOPE OF THE LIMITED
27 LICENSE;
28 (2) THE LICENSEE IS NO LONGER EMPLOYED BY THE HEALTH CARE
29 FACILITY DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (D)(6) OF THIS SECTION;

SENATE BILL 489 7
1 (3) THE LICENSEE PRACTICES MEDICINE OUTSIDE THE STATE
2 WITHOUT BEING LEGALLY AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE MEDICINE IN THE OTHER
3 JURISDICTION;
4 (4) THE LICENSEE HAS BEEN SUBJECT TO A DISCIPLINARY ACTION BY
5 THE HEALTH CARE FACILITY DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (D)(6) OF THIS SECTION OR
6 THE BOARD; OR
7 (5) THE LICENSEE IS NO LONGER ELIGIBLE FOR THE LIMITED
8 LICENSE.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the State Board of Physicians
10 shall consult with MedChi, the Maryland State Medical Society, on the development of
11 policies and regulations implementing this Act.
12 SECTION 2. 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
13 October 1, 2026.
